  The military situations nowadays are slowly switching from human-based operations to automatic control by Artificial Intelligence (AI). It's more concerning now that technologies are capable of choosing and engaging targets without human control. Because of that, many questions are made toward this problem, but the most asked question is whether AI systems should be permitted to exercise lethal force. Although AI is very convenient and brings many advantages for work, the rules or the mandatory guardrails for AI have not been finalized and failed to meet the safety requirements to be able to use it.
